cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CV 

This paper presents a natural language processing approach based on deep learning to automatically identify clinically important recommendations in radiology reports. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to extract relevant information from the reports, making cs.IR a likely sub-category as well. The use of deep learning models also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper involves analysis of a large dataset, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with radiology images, which could also make cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
